On the basis of allegations of possible cover-up of the spread of the epidemic in Iran, more than ten countries had located the origin of their cases in Iran on 28 February, suggesting that the epidemic was perhaps more serious than the 388 cases reported by the Iranian government on that date.
The Iranian parliament was closed, while 23 of its 290 members reported positive testing of the virus on 3 March.
