The Australian authorities evacuated 277 citizens on 3 and 4 February to the Christmas Island detention centre, transformed into a quarantine facility, where they remained for 14 days.
A New Zealand evacuation flight arrived in Auckland on 5 February; its passengers (including from Australia and the Pacific) were quarantined on a naval base at Wangaparaoa, north of Auckland.
